we first we have to flatten for the dense layers, after that we have dense layers that all have the relu activation function I found that other or no activation functions did not work better. The last layer is a softmax layer of 10 since we have 10 categories in the dataset. We use 30 epochs, I tested 1,2,3,4,5,15, 30 and only 30 gave results above 70.

The hardest number to classify seems to be the 3, it is confused with 5,6 and 8, which makes sense as they all follow a structure of 2 circles placed vertically. The 5,6 and 8 are then also confused a lot with each other. Moreover we see that the 1 is confused with 4 and the 7 is confused with 1, but not the other way around. It is more the way numbers have varying ways of being written than the image quality that impacts the accuracy.
